@node Folder configuration
@section Folder configuration

@vindex mu4e-extras-inbox-folder
@vindex mu4e-extras-daily-folder
@vindex mu4e-extras-newsletters-folder
@vindex mu4e-extras-epoch-inbox-folder
@vindex mu4e-extras-epoch-sent-folder
@vindex mu4e-extras-epoch-drafts-folder
@vindex mu4e-extras-epoch-refiled-folder
@vindex mu4e-extras-epoch-trash-folder
The user option @code{mu4e-extras-inbox-folder} specifies the maildir path
for the main inbox folder.  It is used by @code{mu4e-extras-set-shortcuts}
and @code{mu4e-extras-set-bookmarks} to configure maildir shortcuts and
bookmarks (@ref{Setup helpers}).  The default value is an empty string; you
must set this to match your maildir layout (e.g., @samp{"/Inbox"}).

The user option @code{mu4e-extras-daily-folder} specifies the maildir path
for a ``daily'' folder, also used by @code{mu4e-extras-set-shortcuts}.  The
default value is an empty string.

The user option @code{mu4e-extras-newsletters-folder} specifies the maildir
path for a newsletters folder.  The default value is an empty string.
This option is available for use in custom configurations but is not
referenced by any default function in the package.

The user option @code{mu4e-extras-epoch-inbox-folder} specifies the maildir
path for the Epoch AI inbox folder, used by
@code{mu4e-extras-set-shortcuts} and @code{mu4e-extras-set-bookmarks}.  The
default value is an empty string.

The user options @code{mu4e-extras-epoch-sent-folder},
@code{mu4e-extras-epoch-drafts-folder}, @code{mu4e-extras-epoch-refiled-folder},
and @code{mu4e-extras-epoch-trash-folder} specify the maildir paths for the
corresponding Epoch AI folders.  They are used by
@code{mu4e-extras-set-shortcuts} to add uppercase-key maildir shortcuts for
Epoch folders.  The default value for each is an empty string.

@node Reply behavior
@section Reply behavior

@vindex mu4e-extras-wide-reply
The user option @code{mu4e-extras-wide-reply} controls the default behavior
when replying to messages with multiple recipients.  It accepts three
values:

@itemize
@item
@code{prompt} (the default): ask the user whether to reply to all.
@item
@code{t}: always reply to all recipients.
@item
@code{nil}: always reply only to the sender.
@end itemize

This option is consulted by @code{mu4e-extras-compose-reply}
(@ref{Composing messages}).  When the original message has only a single
recipient (excluding the sender), the option has no effect and a normal
reply is always used.

@node Reaction emojis
@section Reaction emojis

@vindex mu4e-extras-reaction-emojis
The user option @code{mu4e-extras-reaction-emojis} specifies the list of
emoji choices presented when reacting to a message with
@code{mu4e-extras-react-to-message} (@ref{Gmail reactions}).  The default value
includes common emojis such as thumbs up, heart, and check mark.

@node Chrome profile selection
@section Chrome profile selection

@vindex mu4e-extras-chrome-profile-personal
@vindex mu4e-extras-chrome-profile-work
@vindex mu4e-extras-chrome-program
Commands that open Gmail in a browser route the URL to a specific
Chrome profile based on the email account.  This is useful when you
run separate Chrome profiles for personal and work browsing.

The user option @code{mu4e-extras-chrome-profile-personal} specifies the
Chrome profile directory for personal email.  The value is the on-disk
directory name inside @samp{~/Library/Application Support/Google/Chrome/}
(e.g. @samp{"Default"}, @samp{"Profile 1"}, @samp{"Profile 2"}), @strong{not} the display
name shown in Chrome's UI@.  Chrome numbers profile directories
sequentially: the first profile is @samp{"Default"}, subsequent profiles
are @samp{"Profile 1"}, @samp{"Profile 2"}, and so on.  The default value is
@samp{"Default"}.

The user option @code{mu4e-extras-chrome-profile-work} specifies the Chrome
profile directory for work (Epoch) email, using the same naming
convention.  The default value is @samp{"Profile 2"}.

The user option @code{mu4e-extras-chrome-program} specifies the Chrome
executable used to open Gmail URLs.  The default value is the standard
macOS Chrome executable path.

These options are consulted by @code{mu4e-extras-chrome-profile-for-msg}
(@ref{Chrome profile helpers}), which is called by @code{mu4e-extras-view-in-gmail},
@code{mu4e-extras-open-gmail}, and @code{mu4e-extras-compose-new-externally}
(@ref{Viewing messages in Gmail}, @ref{Composing messages}).

