@node Read status management
@section Read status management

@findex mu4e-extras-reapply-read-status
@findex mu4e-extras-reapply-read-status-set-timer
@findex mu4e-extras-add-refiled-to-mark-as-read-queue
@findex mu4e-extras-add-sent-to-mark-as-read-queue
@vindex mu4e-extras-mark-as-read-queue
The variable @code{mu4e-extras-mark-as-read-queue} holds a list of message
IDs that need to be re-marked as read after the next Gmail
synchronization.  Messages are added to this queue by two functions:

The function @code{mu4e-extras-add-refiled-to-mark-as-read-queue} adds the
current message to the queue, refiles it, and executes all marks.  It is
called by @code{mu4e-extras-headers-mark-read-and-refile}
(@ref{Marking as read and refiling}).

The function @code{mu4e-extras-add-sent-to-mark-as-read-queue} adds the sent
message's ID to the queue.  It is intended for @code{message-sent-hook}.
Gmail automatically saves a copy of sent messages, and the synced-back
copy appears as unread; this function ensures it is marked as read.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-reapply-read-status} iterates through the
queue and marks each message as seen using @code{mu4e--server-move} with the
@samp{+S-u} flags.  It then clears the queue.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-reapply-read-status-set-timer} sets a
30-second timer to call @code{mu4e-extras-reapply-read-status} if the queue
is not empty.  This delay allows the synchronization to complete before
re-applying the read status.

@node Gmail flag correction
@section Gmail flag correction

@findex mu4e-extras-gmail-fix-flags
The function @code{mu4e-extras-gmail-fix-flags} translates standard @samp{mu4e}
marks into Gmail-specific label changes.  For each mark and message
pair, it applies the appropriate tag operations: removing @samp{\Inbox} and
adding @samp{\Trash} for trash, removing @samp{\Inbox} and adding @samp{\Refiled} for
refile, and toggling @samp{\Starred} for flag/unflag.  Epoch messages are
skipped, since they are synced via the Gmail API directly (through
@samp{gmail-maildir-sync}) rather than via @samp{mbsync}, so IMAP flag
manipulation does not apply to them.

@node Setup helpers
@section Setup helpers

@findex mu4e-extras-set-shortcuts
@findex mu4e-extras-set-bookmarks
@findex mu4e-extras-set-face-locally
@findex mu4e-extras-send-via-gmail-api
@findex mu4e-extras-set-contexts
@findex mu4e-extras-set-index-params
The function @code{mu4e-extras-set-shortcuts} adds predefined entries to
@code{mu4e-maildir-shortcuts}.  Personal folders use lowercase keys (@code{i} for
inbox, @code{y} for daily) and Epoch folders use uppercase keys (@code{I} for
inbox, @code{T} for sent, @code{D} for drafts, @code{R} for refiled, @code{X} for trash).

The function @code{mu4e-extras-set-bookmarks} adds an ``All inboxes'' bookmark
(key @code{a}) to @code{mu4e-bookmarks} that queries both the personal and Epoch
inbox folders, providing a combined view of all incoming mail.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-set-face-locally} remaps the @code{shr-text} face
to a smaller height (0.9) in @code{mu4e-view-mode} buffers.  This is
intended for @code{mu4e-view-mode-hook} to improve the readability of HTML
emails rendered with @samp{shr}.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-send-via-gmail-api} sends the current message
by piping it to @samp{gmail-maildir-sync send}, which uses the Gmail API
directly.  Unlike @code{message-send-mail-with-sendmail}, it does not inject
sendmail-specific flags (@samp{-oi}, @samp{-f}, @samp{-t}) that @samp{gmail-maildir-sync}
does not accept.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-set-contexts} defines and sets
@code{mu4e-contexts} for six combinations: personal HTML, personal plain
text, Epoch HTML, Epoch plain text, Tlon HTML, and Tlon plain text.
Each context uses environment variables (@samp{PERSONAL_GMAIL},
@samp{EPOCH_EMAIL}, @samp{WORK_EMAIL}) for email addresses and references
account-specific signature variables from @samp{org-msg-extras.el}
(@code{org-msg-extras-epoch-html-signature},
@code{org-msg-extras-tlon-html-signature}, etc.).  The Epoch contexts also
set account-specific folder paths (sent, drafts) and use the custom
function @code{mu4e-extras-send-via-gmail-api} to send messages via
@samp{gmail-maildir-sync send} instead of SMTP, since the Epoch Google
Workspace admin has disabled IMAP/SMTP@.  The Tlon contexts
authenticate SMTP as @samp{PERSONAL_GMAIL} (not @samp{WORK_EMAIL}), since
the Tlon account is configured as a send-as alias in Gmail.  The
plain text contexts disable @code{org-msg-mode} on entry and re-enable
it on leave.

@findex mu4e-extras-set-account-folders
The function @code{mu4e-extras-set-account-folders} sets @code{mu4e-refile-folder}
and @code{mu4e-trash-folder} to functions that route messages to the correct
account-specific folder based on the message's maildir path.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-set-index-params} adjusts indexing parameters
(@code{mu4e-index-lazy-check} and @code{mu4e-index-cleanup}) based on Emacs idle
time.  When the user has been idle for longer than
@code{mu4e-update-interval}, it assumes the user is away and performs a
thorough index (lazy check off, cleanup on).  When idle time is short,
it performs a fast index (lazy check on, cleanup off).

@node Archiving refiled messages
@section Archiving refiled messages

@findex mu4e-extras-archive-refiled
The function @code{mu4e-extras-archive-refiled} archives messages that have
the ``refile'' label by running a full mail sync with @samp{mbsync gmail-all}
and performing a thorough index.  This is intended for periodic cleanup
to keep the archive up to date.

@node Context matching
@section Context matching

@findex mu4e-extras-msg-is-personal-p
@findex mu4e-extras-msg-is-epoch-p
@findex mu4e-extras-msg-is-tlon-p
@findex mu4e-extras-msg-belongs-to-epoch-p
@findex mu4e-extras-msg-is-html-p
@findex mu4e-extras-refile-folder
@findex mu4e-extras-trash-folder
The function @code{mu4e-extras-msg-is-personal-p} returns non-@code{nil} if the
message's @samp{:to} field matches either the personal Gmail address or the
personal email address (from environment variables).

The function @code{mu4e-extras-msg-is-epoch-p} returns non-@code{nil} if the
message's @samp{:to} field matches the Epoch AI email address.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-msg-is-tlon-p} returns non-@code{nil} if the
message's @samp{:to} field matches the Tlon work email address or if the
@samp{:reply-to} field matches the team's Google Group.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-msg-belongs-to-epoch-p} returns non-@code{nil} if
the message's maildir path starts with @samp{/epoch/}.  This is used by the
folder routing functions below.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-refile-folder} returns @samp{/epoch/Refiled} for
Epoch messages and @samp{/Refiled} for all others.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-trash-folder} returns @samp{/epoch/Trash} for
Epoch messages and @samp{/Trash} for all others.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-msg-is-html-p} returns non-@code{nil} if the
message contains a @samp{text/html} MIME part, as determined by parsing the
raw message file.

@node Reaction helpers
@section Reaction helpers

@findex mu4e-extras-reaction-from-address
@findex mu4e-extras-reaction-to-email
@findex mu4e-extras-reaction-build-mime
@findex mu4e-extras-reaction-send
The function @code{mu4e-extras-reaction-from-address} determines the
sending account for a reaction by checking which of the user's email
addresses (Epoch, Tlon, or personal) appears in the message's To or
Cc fields.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-reaction-to-email} extracts the bare email
address of the original sender.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-reaction-build-mime} constructs a
@samp{multipart/alternative} MIME message containing three parts: a plain
text fallback, a @samp{text/vnd.google.email-reaction+json} part with the
emoji and format version, and an HTML fallback.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-reaction-send} dispatches the reaction
message to the appropriate transport: the Gmail API (via
@samp{gmail-maildir-sync send}) for Epoch messages, and SMTP for all
others.

@node Chrome profile helpers
@section Chrome profile helpers

@findex mu4e-extras-browse-url-in-chrome-profile
@findex mu4e-extras-chrome-profile-for-msg
@vindex mu4e-extras-chrome-program
The function @code{mu4e-extras-browse-url-in-chrome-profile} opens a URL in
a specific Chrome profile by launching @code{mu4e-extras-chrome-program}
with the @samp{--profile-directory} and @samp{--new-tab} flags.  PROFILE is a
directory name like @samp{"Default"} or @samp{"Profile 2"}.

The function @code{mu4e-extras-chrome-profile-for-msg} returns the Chrome
profile directory for a given message.  It returns
@code{mu4e-extras-chrome-profile-work} for Epoch messages and
@code{mu4e-extras-chrome-profile-personal} otherwise (@ref{Chrome profile selection, , Chrome profile
selection}).  When MSG is @code{nil}, it returns the personal profile.

@node Message file access
@section Message file access

@findex mu4e-extras-get-message-file
The function @code{mu4e-extras-get-message-file} returns the filesystem path
of the message at point.  It checks @code{mu4e-compose-parent-message} first
(for use during composition) and falls back to @code{mu4e-message-at-point}.

